      "verification": {
        "verified": true,
        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree 1d640dd9360bffcf7142a035adcaad2c1be2539c\nparent f0e498af5c0b9978bcd97b26556c83f54beb63f8\nauthor Lőrinc <pap.lorinc@gmail.com> 1776765409 +0200\ncommitter Lőrinc <pap.lorinc@gmail.com> 1776765683 +0200\n\ndbwrapper: use `SpanReader` for iterator keys\n\n`CDBIterator::GetKey()` only deserializes the current LevelDB key once.\n`GetKeyImpl()` already exposes the current key as a contiguous borrowed byte span, and `GetKey()` creates a fresh local reader and only performs immediate forward reads before returning.\n\nSwitch this path to `SpanReader` so the key bytes are read in place instead of being copied into a temporary `DataStream`.\nThis keeps the same exception swallowing and `bool` return semantics while avoiding the extra allocation and copy.\n\nThe preceding test locks down the subtle safety property that matters here: a failed decode must not consume the current iterator entry.\nNote that the same simplification does not apply to `GetValue()`, because that path deobfuscates the value bytes in place first and still needs an owning mutable buffer.\n",
        "signature": "-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\niQIzBAABCAAdFiEEqXy8dDLWkKQdUrTAZp//D/pHenYFAmnnSvMACgkQZp//D/pH\nenaY6RAAxsaMWIl2rfM4hBsXb1YS+BrF+4Z4DivOcHopi1DMN1g600D12vZoNktG\nW7ZCGpc/tuohCFN/kx6RiwFI8LjW/GUFbq9gwU16atda4SSGo9yOH7H/NTYdSurb\nDe8xScGosUdPkM6IM5WvNv0wGdPJ4MAfGeB6Ah5oIaEEygBn8d6T5Fmk2A3sJHEi\n+n2VzGqV/8FftsnWT2ZuowMGgsBhjJZcTX5D0bqCZVh8juQOmBFaJk03aBGIpwKb\ny7XqQzUPMZNfgo7nPCq9lMzEAsI+Rasb61D0a9gQiJcYLsIYlo7A7F+1ETvdXhgi\nSauj2FHqdaO5Bay/KI2Win+yZWQuUMQrxJ2gL765uDDT9jKjxFjKEulcNGydHUhB\nLp72EIrHFz4P+Y1fyZLuoxgayV3RbvqYMGu4h+Q0lSYuamILtrgjM1SvSrSBFh5H\nkojW5G8jCGRIel7Eo4tAv6UVdbdgway9WEFpPQJRrfqymPm5okYODUecgYYjJ/ZD\nkNUwt5ElK9NgwBCtqAiClOKtYMDCBlCyKoK94elNlpwWzYArP68QLcboA5T0iiv7\nmjY33I2101GixTHTGi2SC65nnrw1y2y3yH+faIGr1mYfJKDEwjJaRBvN2LO8KYDu\nTgOqLxJOoIXnG2p2P1IPrEd7S84hN/aLVytUoazwXx1di/eR1zw=\n=WVN0\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----"
